com.salesforce.omakase.ast.collection

Class LinkedSyntaxCollection<P,T extends Groupable<P,T>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.salesforce.omakase.ast.collection.LinkedSyntaxCollection<P,T>
  • Type Parameters:
    P - Type of the (P)arent object containing this collection (e.g., SelectorParts have Selectors as the parent).
    T - The (T)ype of units to be grouped with.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    SyntaxCollection<P,T>, Iterable<T>

    public final class LinkedSyntaxCollection<P,T extends Groupable<P,T>>
extends Object
implements SyntaxCollection<P,T>
    Standard (default) implementation of the SyntaxCollection.

    This uses a linked-node approach optimized for random lookups, insertions and removals. Uniqueness is maintained like a set and prevents duplicates. Appending or prepending an existing unit will simply move its position.
